Serves 4-6Ingredients:1 small green cabbage1 small red cabbage250ml (1 cup) mayonnaise30ml (2 tbsp) cake flourPinch of saltPinch of freshly ground black pepper500ml (2 cups) plain yoghurt4 large eggs30g (2 tbsp) finely grated parmesan4 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only30ml (3 tbsp) olive oil100g chorizo sausage, cubed8-10 cocktail tomatoes, quartered50g ( cup) pine nuts or almondsTonight's supper: Banting-friendly fishcakesMethod:1) Preheat the oven to 180 C.2) Cut the cabbages into thick slices, trying to keep the pieces together.3) In a mixing bowl, whisk the mayonnaise, flour and seasoning together. Add the yoghurt, eggs, parmesan and half the thyme leaves and whisk until well combined. Pour mixture into a greased ovenproof dish and arrange the cabbage slices in alternating layers on top. Bake for 30 minutes.4) While the pie is baking, heat the olive oil in a pan and fry the chorizo cubes until brown. Remove pie from oven and top with the chorizo, tomatoes, pine nuts and remaining thyme leaves. Bake for another 15 minutes or until set, covering with foil if it browns too fast.